---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const nonce = Astro.locals.cspNonce;
---

<Layout
  title="StripMeta"
  category="CYBER-OPSEC"
  categoryHref="/wiki/Sécurite-Numerique"
  description="Épurateur de métadonnées EXIF/XMP/IPTC 100% client-side. Aucune image ne quitte ton navigateur. JPEG, PNG, WebP."
>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     EN-TÊTE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="sm-header">
  <div class="sm-badge">⊡ OUTIL CYBER-OPSEC</div>
  <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
    <h1 class="sm-title">StripMeta</h1>
    <button id="smGuideBtn" class="sm-guide-open-btn" aria-label="Ouvrir le guide">
      <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true">
        <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4m0-4h.01" stroke-linecap="round"/>
      </svg>
      Guide
    </button>
  </div>
  <p class="sm-subtitle">Inspecter puis supprimer · EXIF · XMP · IPTC · GPS · ICC profiles · Thumbnails embarqués</p>
  <div class="sm-local-notice">
    <span class="sm-notice-icon">⚿</span>
    <span>Tes images ne quittent <strong>jamais ton navigateur</strong>. Tout le traitement est local. Aucun pixel ne transite vers un serveur.</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     GUIDE MODAL
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="sm-guide-overlay"
  class="fixed inset-0 z-50 hidden"
  style="background:rgba(5,5,10,0.93);backdrop-filter:blur(4px);">

  <div class="absolute inset-y-0 right-0 w-full max-w-xl flex flex-col"
    style="background:#08080c;border-left:1px solid #2a2a3a;overflow-y:auto;">

    <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-4 border-b border-dedsec-border sticky top-0 z-10"
      style="background:#08080c;">
      <div>
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-dedsec-muted tracking-widest uppercase mb-0.5">Documentation</div>
        <div class="font-bold text-neon-green" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-size:18px;">StripMeta - Guide</div>
      </div>
      <button id="smGuideClose" aria-label="Fermer"
        class="text-dedsec-muted hover:text-neon-green transition-colors font-mono text-xl leading-none p-1">×</button>
    </div>

    <div class="px-6 py-6 space-y-7" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;">

      <section>
        <div class="sm-guide-section-title">Qu'est-ce que c'est</div>
        <p class="text-dedsec-text/90 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          StripMeta supprime toutes les métadonnées embarquées dans tes images avant que tu les partages. Ces métadonnées peuvent contenir : les coordonnées GPS exactes où la photo a été prise, le modèle de ton téléphone et son numéro de série, la date et l'heure précises, ton logiciel d'édition, et parfois une miniature non éditée de l'image originale.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <div class="sm-guide-section-title">Ce que contient une photo non nettoyée</div>
        <div class="space-y-2 mt-2">
          {[
            { level: 'critical', label: 'GPS (lat/lon)', detail: 'Localisation exacte à quelques mètres. Révèle l\'adresse, le site, le trajet.' },
            { level: 'high',     label: 'Device ID',     detail: 'Marque, modèle, numéro de série de l\'appareil. Permet l\'identification croisée.' },
            { level: 'high',     label: 'Timestamp',     detail: 'Date et heure exactes de la prise de vue. Reconstitue une timeline.' },
            { level: 'med',      label: 'Thumbnail EXIF',detail: 'Miniature de l\'image AVANT retouche. Si tu as flouté un visage, la miniature peut l\'avoir gardé net.' },
            { level: 'med',      label: 'Logiciel',      detail: 'Version de Lightroom, Photoshop, OS - fingerprinting de l\'environnement.' },
            { level: 'low',      label: 'ICC Profile',   detail: 'Profil colorimétrique - fingerprinting de l\'écran/appareil.' },
            { level: 'low',      label: 'XMP / IPTC',    detail: 'Commentaires, auteur, copyright, légendes ajoutées par un logiciel d\'édition.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start text-sm">
              <span class={
                item.level === 'critical' ? 'font-mono text-[9px] border px-1.5 py-0.5 shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-red-400 border-red-400/50 bg-red-400/08' :
                item.level === 'high'     ? 'font-mono text-[9px] border px-1.5 py-0.5 shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-orange-400 border-orange-400/50 bg-orange-400/08' :
                item.level === 'med'      ? 'font-mono text-[9px] border px-1.5 py-0.5 shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-yellow-400/80 border-yellow-400/40 bg-yellow-400/05' :
                                            'font-mono text-[9px] border px-1.5 py-0.5 shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-dedsec-muted border-dedsec-border'
              }>{item.level.toUpperCase()}</span>
              <div>
                <span class="text-dedsec-text/90 font-medium">{item.label}</span>
                <span class="text-dedsec-muted"> - {item.detail}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <div class="sm-guide-section-title">Inspection avant nettoyage</div>
        <p class="text-dedsec-text/90 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Dès que tu déposes une image, StripMeta lit ses métadonnées sans rien modifier et affiche ce que le fichier expose : des pastilles de risque (GPS, appareil, date, numéro de série, logiciel) apparaissent sur la carte, et le détail complet est listé dans un tableau. Si des coordonnées GPS sont présentes, la carte s'ouvre automatiquement et te montre le point exact sur OpenStreetMap. Tu vois donc le danger réel avant de décider, puis tu nettoies le fichier d'un clic. La lecture est, comme le reste, entièrement locale.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <div class="sm-guide-section-title">Méthode de nettoyage</div>
        <p class="text-dedsec-text/90 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          StripMeta utilise deux techniques complémentaires pour garantir un nettoyage complet :
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="sm-method-block">
            <div class="sm-method-title">1. Parsing binaire (JPEG/PNG)</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-dedsec-muted leading-relaxed">Lecture octet par octet du fichier. Identification et suppression chirurgicale des segments de métadonnées (APP1 EXIF, APP1 XMP, APP13 IPTC pour JPEG ; chunks tEXt, iTXt, zTXt, eXIf pour PNG) sans toucher aux données d'image.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="sm-method-block">
            <div class="sm-method-title">2. Re-encodage Canvas (filet de sécurité)</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-dedsec-muted leading-relaxed">L'image est dessinée dans un canvas HTML5 et re-exportée. Le canvas ne transporte aucune métadonnée. Garantit un résultat propre même si des métadonnées sont encodées de façon non standard.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sm-guide-opsec mt-4">
          <span class="sm-guide-opsec-icon">⚠</span>
          <div class="text-sm text-dedsec-muted leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-yellow-400/80">Limite connue :</strong> le re-encodage JPEG introduit une légère perte de qualité (contrôlable via le curseur). Pour les images qui ne peuvent pas tolérer de perte, utilise le mode PNG en sortie.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <div class="sm-guide-section-title">Formats supportés</div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mt-2">
          {[
            { fmt: 'JPEG', status: 'full', detail: 'Parsing EXIF + re-encodage Canvas' },
            { fmt: 'PNG',  status: 'full', detail: 'Suppression chunks + re-encodage' },
            { fmt: 'WebP', status: 'canvas', detail: 'Re-encodage Canvas uniquement' },
            { fmt: 'HEIC/HEIF', status: 'warn', detail: 'Converti en JPEG en sortie' },
            { fmt: 'TIFF', status: 'warn', detail: 'Converti en JPEG en sortie' },
            { fmt: 'GIF',  status: 'no', detail: 'Non supporté' },
          ].map(f => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono">
              <span class={
                f.status === 'full'   ? 'text-neon-green' :
                f.status === 'canvas' ? 'text-yellow-400/80' :
                f.status === 'warn'   ? 'text-orange-400' : 'text-dedsec-muted/50'
              }>{f.status === 'full' ? '●' : f.status === 'canvas' ? '◐' : f.status === 'warn' ? '◌' : '○'}</span>
              <span class="text-dedsec-text/80 w-16 shrink-0">{f.fmt}</span>
              <span class="text-dedsec-muted/70">{f.detail}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     ZONE DE DROP
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="sm-dropzone"
  class="sm-dropzone"
  role="button"
  tabindex="0"
  aria-label="Zone de dépôt de fichiers">
  <div class="sm-drop-inner">
    <div class="sm-drop-icon">⊞</div>
    <div class="sm-drop-title">Dépose tes images ici</div>
    <div class="sm-drop-sub">JPEG · PNG · WebP · HEIC · TIFF · ou clique pour sélectionner</div>
    <div class="sm-drop-sub" style="margin-top:4px;font-size:10px;color:rgba(122,122,138,0.5);">Plusieurs fichiers acceptés · Aucune donnée ne quitte le navigateur</div>
  </div>
  <input id="sm-file-input" type="file" accept="image/*" multiple class="hidden" aria-hidden="true" />
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     OPTIONS GLOBALES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="sm-options" class="hidden sm-options-bar">
  <div class="sm-opt-group">
    <label class="sm-opt-label" for="sm-quality">Qualité JPEG sortie</label>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
      <input id="sm-quality" type="range" min="70" max="99" value="92" class="sm-range" />
      <span id="sm-quality-val" class="font-mono text-neon-green text-sm w-8">92</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sm-opt-group">
    <label class="sm-opt-label">Format de sortie</label>
    <div class="flex gap-2">
      <button class="sm-fmt-btn active" data-fmt="original">Original</button>
      <button class="sm-fmt-btn" data-fmt="jpeg">JPEG</button>
      <button class="sm-fmt-btn" data-fmt="png">PNG</button>
      <button class="sm-fmt-btn" data-fmt="webp">WebP</button>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sm-opt-group">
    <label class="sm-opt-label">Renommer les fichiers</label>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
      <div id="sm-rename-toggle" class="sm-toggle" role="switch" aria-checked="false" tabindex="0">
        <div class="sm-toggle-thumb"></div>
      </div>
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-dedsec-muted">Ajouter suffixe <code class="text-neon-green/70">_clean</code></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     LISTE DES FICHIERS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="sm-file-list" class="hidden space-y-3 mb-6"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     ACTIONS GLOBALES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="sm-actions" class="hidden sm-actions-bar">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
    <button id="sm-process-all" class="sm-btn-primary">
      <span>⊘</span> Nettoyer tout
    </button>
    <button id="sm-download-all" class="sm-btn-secondary hidden">
      <span>↓</span> Télécharger tout (ZIP)
    </button>
    <button id="sm-clear-all" class="sm-btn-ghost">
      <span>×</span> Vider
    </button>
  </div>
  <div id="sm-global-status" class="text-xs font-mono text-dedsec-muted"></div>
</div>

</Layout>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     STYLES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<style is:global>

/* ── Header ── */
.sm-header { margin-bottom: 32px; }
.sm-badge {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase;
  color: rgba(0,255,159,0.7); border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,159,0.25);
  display: inline-block; padding: 3px 8px; margin-bottom: 10px;
}
.sm-title {
  font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
  font-size: clamp(28px,5vw,42px); font-weight: 800;
  color: #e8e8f0; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: 0 0 6px;
}
.sm-subtitle {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  font-size: 12px; color: rgba(122,122,138,0.85); margin-bottom: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}
.sm-local-notice {
  display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,159,0.2);
  border-left: 3px solid rgba(0,255,159,0.6);
  background: rgba(0,255,159,0.04);
  font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
  font-size: 12.5px; color: rgba(232,232,240,0.75);
}
.sm-notice-icon { font-size: 16px; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px; }
.sm-guide-open-btn {
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
  padding: 6px 12px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,159,0.25);
  background: transparent; color: rgba(0,255,159,0.7);
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase;
  cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s ease;
}
.sm-guide-open-btn:hover { border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.6); color: #00ff9f; background: rgba(0,255,159,0.06); }

/* ── Guide ── */
.sm-guide-section-title {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(0,255,159,0.6);
  margin-bottom: 10px; padding-bottom: 6px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.6);
}
.sm-method-block {
  border: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.8); border-left: 2px solid rgba(0,255,159,0.3);
  padding: 10px 14px; background: rgba(8,8,12,0.5);
}
.sm-method-title {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700;
  color: rgba(0,255,159,0.7); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.sm-guide-opsec {
  display: flex; gap: 10px; padding: 10px 14px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,180,0,0.2); background: rgba(255,160,0,0.05);
}
.sm-guide-opsec-icon { flex-shrink: 0; font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,180,0,0.7); margin-top: 1px; }

/* ── Dropzone ── */
.sm-dropzone {
  border: 2px dashed rgba(0,255,159,0.25);
  background: rgba(0,255,159,0.02);
  padding: 48px 24px;
  text-align: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  position: relative;
}
.sm-dropzone:hover,
.sm-dropzone.drag-over {
  border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.6);
  background: rgba(0,255,159,0.05);
}
.sm-drop-icon { font-size: 36px; color: rgba(0,255,159,0.35); margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1; }
.sm-drop-title { font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: rgba(232,232,240,0.7); margin-bottom: 6px; }
.sm-drop-sub { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: rgba(122,122,138,0.6); letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

/* ── Options bar ── */
.sm-options-bar {
  display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 24px; align-items: center;
  padding: 14px 18px; border: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.8);
  background: rgba(8,8,12,0.5); margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.sm-opt-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
.sm-opt-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(122,122,138,0.7); }
.sm-range { -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; width: 120px; height: 3px; background: rgba(42,42,58,1); outline: none; }
.sm-range::-webkit-slider-thumb { -webkit-appearance: none; width: 14px; height: 14px; background: #00ff9f; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 0; }
.sm-fmt-btn {
  padding: 5px 10px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;
  border: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.8); background: transparent;
  color: rgba(122,122,138,0.7); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s;
}
.sm-fmt-btn:hover { border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.4); color: rgba(0,255,159,0.8); }
.sm-fmt-btn.active { border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.6); color: #00ff9f; background: rgba(0,255,159,0.06); }
.sm-toggle {
  width: 36px; height: 20px; border: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.9);
  background: rgba(8,8,12,0.8); cursor: pointer; position: relative;
  transition: background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
}
.sm-toggle[aria-checked="true"] { background: rgba(0,255,159,0.15); border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.4); }
.sm-toggle-thumb {
  position: absolute; top: 3px; left: 3px; width: 12px; height: 12px;
  background: rgba(122,122,138,0.5); transition: transform 0.2s, background 0.2s;
}
.sm-toggle[aria-checked="true"] .sm-toggle-thumb { transform: translateX(16px); background: #00ff9f; }

/* ── File card ── */
.sm-file-card {
  border: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.8);
  background: rgba(8,8,12,0.5);
  transition: border-color 0.2s;
}
.sm-file-card.state-done { border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.25); }
.sm-file-card.state-error { border-color: rgba(255,68,68,0.3); }
.sm-file-card.state-warn { border-color: rgba(255,180,0,0.3); }

.sm-card-head {
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
  padding: 12px 16px; cursor: pointer; user-select: none;
}
.sm-card-head:hover { background: rgba(0,255,159,0.02); }
.sm-thumb {
  width: 44px; height: 44px; object-fit: cover; flex-shrink: 0;
  border: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.8);
}
.sm-card-info { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
.sm-card-name { font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: #e8e8f0; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }
.sm-card-meta { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; color: rgba(122,122,138,0.7); margin-top: 2px; }
.sm-card-status {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 3px 7px; border: 1px solid; flex-shrink: 0;
}
.sm-card-status.pending  { color: rgba(122,122,138,0.7); border-color: rgba(42,42,58,0.9); }
.sm-card-status.working  { color: rgba(0,255,159,0.7);   border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.3); animation: sm-pulse 0.8s ease-in-out infinite; }
.sm-card-status.done     { color: rgba(0,255,159,1);     border-color: rgba(0,255,159,0.5); background: rgba(0,255,159,0.05); }
.sm-card-status.error    { color: rgba(255,68,68,0.9);   border-color: rgba(255,68,68,0.4); }
.sm-card-status.warn     { color: rgba(255,180,0,0.9);   border-color: rgba(255,180,0,0.4); }
@keyframes sm-pulse { 0%,100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.5; } }

.sm-card-body { display: none; padding: 0 16px 16px; }
.sm-card-body.open { display: block; }

/* Alerte GPS */
.sm-gps-alert {
  display: flex; gap: 10px; padding: 10px 14px; margin-bottom: 12px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,68,68,0.5); border-left: 3px solid rgba(255,68,68,0.8);
  background: rgba(255,68,68,0.06);
}
.sm-gps-alert-icon { font-size: 16px; flex-shrink: 0; }
.sm-gps-alert-title { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: rgba(255,68,68,0.9); text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.sm-gps-alert-val { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: rgba(255,68,68,0.7); }
.sm-gps-maps-link { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; color: rgba(255,68,68,0.6); text-decoration: underline; margin-top: 3px; display: inline-block; }

/* Rapport de métadonnées */
.sm-meta-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 11px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.sm-meta-table th {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(122,122,138,0.7);
  text-align: left; padding: 5px 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.8);
}
.sm-meta-table td {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px;
  padding: 5px 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(42,42,58,0.4);
  vertical-align: top;
}
.sm-meta-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
.sm-meta-table td:first-child { color: rgba(122,122,138,0.7); width: 38%; }
.sm-meta-table td:nth-child(2) { color: rgba(232,232,240,0.75); word-break: break-all; }
.sm-meta-tag-gps    { color: rgba(255,68,68,0.85) !important; }
.sm-meta-tag-device { color: rgba(255,140,0,0.85) !important; }
.sm-meta-tag-soft   { color: rgba(255,220,0,0.75) !important; }

.sm-no-meta {
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px;
  color: rgba(122,122,138,0.5); font-style: italic; padding: 8px 0;
}

/* Stats du nettoyage */
.sm-clean-stats {
  display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; padding: 10px 0; margin-bottom: 12px;
